item.dc:creator: @deans1243 deans1243
item.description:
@deans1243 wrote:

what he said^^ . whats your server 317 508 562!!! and what is it delts? pi etc…?

a basic item command for a project insanity source would look like this

if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("???") && (c.playerRights >=0) { if (c.inWild()) return; c.getItems().addItem(@@@@, &&); }
if it was delta you would take of the word player in playercommand.
replace the ??? with the word of the command. replace the @@@ with the item id you want and eplace the && with the amount of the item the command gives you.

a basic teleport command for project insanity would look like this

if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("?????")) { c.getPA().movePlayer(Y-COORD, X-COORD, 0); }
i hope that helped i just did pi commands well idk why i did thats what im using so im familiar with it and alot of people are switching to pi now.

there dastan i helped...
